<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-31T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-31T07:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/5–3146: Circular
                            telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular
                                Officers</gloss></hi><note n="54" xml:id="d397fn1">At Berlin,
                                London, and Paris.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-31T08:00:00-04:00">May 31, 1946—8
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Pauley reports Chistiakov has prearranged tour for mission with all
                            movements heavily guarded. Mission not allowed visit two major <pb facs="0538" n="526" xml:id="pg_526"/> areas north Korea, denied
                            access certain plants other areas, not permitted split into groups to
                            accomplish mission in 5 days allowed. <gloss target="#t_Sov1">Sov</gloss>s forbidden members take any photographs on official
                                trips.<note n="55" xml:id="d397fn2">Mr. Pauley left Seoul for
                                Mukden, Manchuria, on June 14.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>